By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Former Vice President of Nigeria, Atiku Abubakar has reacted to the death of 14 people at Borno IDP camp on Thursday due to a fire outbreak. It was gathered that no fewer than 700 shelters were destroyed by fire in an Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) camp at Mafa Local Government Area of Borno State. Reacting, the former vice president in a tweet via his Twitter account on Friday, expressed sadness over the unfortunate incident. He said, ”The loss of over a dozen lives in a fire at the IDP camp in Ngala, Borno State, leaving scores injured and hundreds homeless makes me sad. ”May the souls of the deceased rest in peace. ”I hope that help will be expedited for the injured and homeless.” By Rabiu Sani Maiduguri -  The National Emergency Management Agency  (NEMA) on Tuesday confirmed that six persons were killed in a fire outbreak at Rann Internally Displaced Persons  (IDPs) camp in Kala Balge Local Government Area of Borno. NEMA’s North-East Coordinator, Alhaji Bashir Garga, told the News Agency of Nigeria… March 27, 2018 In "News" By Johnson Eyiangho   Mongunu    -      Over 35,000 Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) have so far returned to their ancestral homes from various camps in Borno North in the last two weeks, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports. NAN quoted the Chief of Army Staff, Lt.-Gen. Tukur Buratai as giving… July 8, 2018 In "News" MAIDUGURI - Vice President Yemi Osinbajo on Wednesday commended Borno Government for its efforts at ensuring welfare of Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in the state. Osinbajo made the commendation while speaking with newsmen during a visit to Maiduguri. He said his visit was based on the instruction of President Muhammadu… July 1, 2015 In "News"